verb.description: Interpolate (an intercalary period) in a calendar.
examples: a system was introduced to intercalate an extra month in the calendar

verb.description: Insert (something) between layers in a crystal lattice, geological formation, or other structure.
examples: the interlayer spaces of the graphite host lattice are filled with intercalated layers

origin: Early 17th century: from Latin intercalat- proclaimed as inserted in the calendar, from the verb intercalare, from inter- between + calare proclaim solemnly.
